OL,7,FResearchers at the University of
OL,8,FBristol, who submitted the complaint,
OL,9,Fallege that the posts breach the
OL,10,FCommittee of Advertising Practice
OL,11,F(CAP) Code, which prohibits gambling
OL,12,Fmarketing from having a "strong appeal
OL,13,Fto children."
OL,15,FThey say the social media posts are
OL,16,Fpart of a strategy known as 'content
OL,17,Fmarketing' where companies share
OL,18,Fmaterial online which doesn't
OL,19,Fexplicitly advertise their product,
OL,20,Fbut which is designed to be shareable
OL,21,Fand often funny.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/14
